    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@netnazgul There are multiple levels of selection priority - it's a continuum. The default is `10` and it goes down from there (harvester has `7` for example, MCV has `4`, base buildings have `2`). That's why I added the two new properties to the trait, to explicitly include/exclude actors from selection modes. Otherwise it would have to be an arbitrary less-than-greater-than comparison.\r\n\r\nI have the same concerns regarding the \"special\" mode. Probably it should be restricted to non-combat units (i.e. the ones with priority below `10`).\r\n\r\nI really wanted to do something about aircraft though as it's a pain selecting them over blobs. There are only two mod keys available `Alt` and `Ctrl` and the combination `Alt+Ctrl` which could serve as a third mode. But a third mode would be even more confusing... It's more logical to have `Alt+Ctrl` combine the functions of both. "
  },
