    "created_at": "2018-11-13T14:55:29Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-11-13T14:55:29Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Player opinion: Use normal/special/(harvesters) attributes for selection priorities.\r\n\r\nThe only moment when I use selection priorities to select/include units is when i want all my harvesters on the screen to run for their lives. More often it is used to exclude units from a selection. It would be OK for me if you could select special units together with other special units (instead of having a priority group for each, like harvesters perhaps should have though). Modders could add their own categories.\r\n\r\nNot a fan of a \"support\" or  \"air\" category: \r\n\r\nI want medics to be selectable with combat infantry. Air units are almost always hotkeyed (mean you could exclude them) but sometimes I want to move a blob and have a heli hover over it, so I want to select the heli, too.\r\n\r\nI don't want to include engineers when I select my army, same goes for harvesters. Sometimes I think it would be better to have Tanya not selected in a huge blob (I should probably hotkey her)."
  },
