    "created_at": "2018-11-13T15:50:38Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-11-13T15:50:38Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I'm having the same thoughts as a player. And I've seen similar thought on discord.\r\n\r\nTo summarize, there are several use-cases/complaints:\r\n(1) Select combat and non-combat units together (e.g. moving army and MCV; moving infantry and engie)\r\n(2) Select low priority units independently (e.g. rescue harvesters/MCV/engie)\r\n(3) Select ground units without touching aircraft\r\n(4) Select aircraft without touching ground units\r\n\r\nCase 1 is solved by the \"select all\" mode (`Ctrl+drag`)\r\n\r\nCase 2 is solved by \"select non-combat/special/support\" mode (`Alt+drag`)\r\n\r\nCase 3 can be solved by giving aircraft a lower priority (`9` for example)\r\n\r\nCase 4 would then have the same solution as case 2 (`Alt+drag`)"
  },
